<p>Fresh clashes along the Afghanistan–Pakistan frontier left at least 15 Afghan civilians dead and more than 100 wounded, according to Afghan officials, amid exchanges of fire reported on Wednesday and Tuesday in multiple border sectors [france24.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][thehindu.com#1][dw.com#1]. The flare-up spanned the Spin Boldak district in southeastern Afghanistan and Pakistan’s Chaman district across the border [aljazeera.com#1]. Islamabad said Afghan forces opened &quot;unprovoked fire&quot; that was repulsed, while the Taliban administration accused Pakistan of launching attacks with light and heavy weapons [ndtv.com#1][abcnews.go.com#2][firstpost.com#1]. Tensions have risen since explosions in Afghanistan last week, including in Kabul, that were blamed on Pakistan; Pakistan, for its part, accuses Afghanistan of sheltering militants who mount attacks inside Pakistan [france24.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. In a potential opening for de-escalation, President Trump signaled he is willing to help resolve the dispute [firstpost.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/o_0nvzhiE_RImoFLFo5UoUMlJ61TBp8SPabUw-dI-mgANzFB8xp6mFRjcQz7bFgh3TWBbt-_gbmqDMZ7b8M9UyW8tz0G7qBxkOI1kvDvjGchtJX3-EyKv5rSQWINWORn7O8yIn6xEuhad-lws8jRDX2UDABKYlXbftUBgqvrEg' alt='Border region between Afghanistan and Pakistan amid heightened tensions.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Casualty toll: Afghan officials reported at least 15 civilians killed and over 100 wounded in the renewed fighting [france24.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1][thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Competing claims: Pakistan said Afghan forces opened &quot;unprovoked&quot; fire that was repelled, while the Taliban said Pakistan launched attacks using light and heavy weapons [ndtv.com#1][abcnews.go.com#2][firstpost.com#1].</li><li>Clash hotspots: The brief flare-up spanned Afghanistan’s Spin Boldak (Kandahar) and Pakistan’s Chaman (Balochistan) districts along the border [aljazeera.com#1].</li><li>Rising tensions: Violence has intensified since explosions in Afghanistan last week, including in Kabul, that were blamed on Pakistan, while Islamabad accuses Kabul of harboring militants [france24.com#1][thehindu.com#1].</li><li>Possible mediation: President Trump expressed willingness to step in to help resolve the dispute [firstpost.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Taliban government (Afghanistan): Officials say more than a dozen Afghan civilians were killed and over 100 wounded, and accuse Pakistan of firing across the border. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/afghanistan-dozen-civilians-killed-renewed-border-fighting-pakistan-126537114'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>Government of Pakistan: State-run media reported Afghan troops opened &quot;unprovoked&quot; fire, which Pakistani forces repulsed. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/pakistan-reports-fresh-clash-with-afghan-forces-following-unprovoked-fire-9458080#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li><li>United States (President Trump): The President indicated he is willing to step in and help resolve the border conflict. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/pakistan-border-clashes-afghanistan-trump-intervention-13942277.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/asia-pacific/20251015-deadly-border-clashes-afghanistan-pakistan-ttp'>New border clashes between Afghanistan and Pakistan kill at least 15</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/pakistan-border-clashes-afghanistan-trump-intervention-13942277.html'>Is Pakistan stoking border clashes with Afghanistan that Trump wants to solve?</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/pakistan-fresh-clashes-on-afghan-border-leave-several-dead/a-74364795'>Pakistan: Fresh clashes on Afghan border leave several dead</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/pakistan-reports-fresh-clash-with-afghan-forces-following-unprovoked-fire-9458080#publisher=newsstand'